Jeremy Mansfield says that the lessons he learned growing up helped to shape his life and his career. JOHANNESBURG - Jeremy Mansfield has shared his hopes, fears and attitude about money. Speaking to Bruce Whitfield on Talk Radio702, Mansfield says he grew up in a household where he was taught the importance of saving. “If you wanted something, you saved up for it and then you bought it. I was really fortunate; I was educated by my parents through school and university, so I had that grounding.” As a result of his upbringing, Mansfield said this also taught him his entrepreneurial skills into becoming the money-maker that he is today. Listen to the audio below for more. 